01:02:03,091 --> 01:02:05,552
Have you ever embraced someone
dying of plague, sire?

515
01:02:12,475 --> 01:02:18,064
No, but if you interrupt me again,
I assure you that you shall.

516
01:02:18,148 --> 01:02:21,109
Senator, my brother
is very tired.

517
01:02:21,151 --> 01:02:23,737
Leave your list with me.

518
01:02:23,820 --> 01:02:26,489
Caesar shall do
all that Rome requires.

519
01:02:26,573 --> 01:02:31,453
My lady, as always,
your lightest touch commands obedience.

520
01:02:38,418 --> 01:02:41,004
Who are they
to lecture me?

521
01:02:41,087 --> 01:02:43,673
Commodus, the Senate has its uses.

522
01:02:43,757 --> 01:02:46,510
What uses?
All they do is talk.

523
01:02:47,969 --> 01:02:50,972
It should be just...
you and me...

524
01:02:51,056 --> 01:02:53,600
- and Rome.
- Don't even think it!

525
01:02:53,683 --> 01:02:56,102
There's always
been a Senate.

526
01:02:56,186 --> 01:03:00,482
Rome has changed.
It takes an emperor...

527
01:03:00,565 --> 01:03:03,401
-to rule an empire.
-Of course, but leave the people their-

528
01:03:03,443 --> 01:03:06,071
Illusions.

529
01:03:06,154 --> 01:03:08,406
Traditions.

530
01:03:08,490 --> 01:03:11,743
My father's war
against the barbarians-

531
01:03:11,826 --> 01:03:14,538
He said it himself,
it achieved nothing.

532
01:03:14,621 --> 01:03:17,749
- But the people loved him.
- The people always love victories.

533
01:03:17,832 --> 01:03:22,712
Why? They didn't see the battles.

534
01:03:22,796 --> 01:03:26,758
- What do they care about Germania?
- They care about the greatness of Rome.

535
01:03:26,800 --> 01:03:30,720
The greatness of Rome.

536
01:03:30,804 --> 01:03:33,515
Well, what is that?

537
01:03:35,225 --> 01:03:39,354
It's an idea-
greatness.

538
01:03:42,440 --> 01:03:46,653
- Greatness is a vision.
- Exactly. A vision.

539
01:03:47,821 --> 01:03:51,408
Do you not see, Lucilla?

540
01:03:51,491 --> 01:03:56,121
I will give the people a vision of Rome,
and they'll love me for it.

541
01:03:56,204 --> 01:04:00,750
And they'll soon forget the tedious
sermonizing of a few dry, old men.

542
01:04:12,304 --> 01:04:15,557
I will give the people
the greatest vision of their lives.

543
01:05:05,357 --> 01:05:09,402
Vino, vino, vino!
White and red wine
for your drinking pleasure!

544
01:05:11,696 --> 01:05:17,536
Vino, vino, vino! Red and white wine
for your drinking pleasure!

545
01:05:17,577 --> 01:05:19,538
Games.

546
01:05:21,331 --> 01:05:24,251
1 50 days of games.

547
01:05:24,334 --> 01:05:27,963
- He's cleverer than I thought.
- Oh, clever.

548
01:05:28,046 --> 01:05:30,715
The whole of Rome would
be laughing at him...

549
01:05:30,799 --> 01:05:33,385
if they weren't so afraid
of his Praetorians.

550
01:05:33,468 --> 01:05:36,930
Fear and wonder-
a powerful combination.

551
01:05:37,013 --> 01:05:39,850
You really think the people
are going to be seduced by that?

552
01:05:39,933 --> 01:05:44,229
I think he knows what Rome is.
Rome is the mob.

553
01:05:44,271 --> 01:05:47,607
Conjure magic for them,
and they'll be distracted.

554
01:05:47,649 --> 01:05:51,736
Take away their freedom
and still they'll roar.

555
01:05:51,778 --> 01:05:54,364
The beating heart
of Rome...

556
01:05:54,447 --> 01:05:56,658
is not the marble
of the Senate.

557
01:05:56,741 --> 01:05:59,119
It's the sand
of the Colosseum.

558
01:06:00,203 --> 01:06:02,497
He'll bring them death,

559
01:06:04,082 --> 01:06:06,877
and they will
love him for it.

560
01:06:11,047 --> 01:06:15,635
Spaniard! Spaniard!
Spaniard! Spaniard!

561
01:06:28,148 --> 01:06:30,358
Spaniard.

562
01:06:30,442 --> 01:06:32,861
- Spain.
- Spaniard.
- Spaniard.

563
01:06:32,903 --> 01:06:36,072
- Spaniard.
- Spaniard.
- Spaniard.

564
01:06:37,782 --> 01:06:39,701
Guard!

565
01:07:42,848 --> 01:07:45,642
- Are you not entertained?

566
01:07:45,725 --> 01:07:47,978
Are you not entertained?

567
01:07:50,522 --> 01:07:53,233
Is this not why you are here?

568
01:07:57,737 --> 01:08:01,241
Spaniard! Spaniard!
Spaniard! Spaniard!

569
01:08:01,324 --> 01:08:05,620
Spaniard! Spaniard! Spaniard! Spaniard!

570
01:08:08,248 --> 01:08:10,625
Spaniard! Spaniard! Spaniard!

571
01:08:10,709 --> 01:08:14,713
Spaniard! Spaniard!
Spaniard! Spaniard!

572
01:08:17,048 --> 01:08:19,926
What do you want?

573
01:08:20,010 --> 01:08:22,012
Huh?

574
01:08:22,095 --> 01:08:24,014
Girl?

575
01:08:24,097 --> 01:08:26,016
Boy?

576
01:08:26,099 --> 01:08:29,227
- You sent for me?
- Yes, I did.

577
01:08:29,311 --> 01:08:32,480
You're good, Spaniard,
but you're not that good.

578
01:08:32,564 --> 01:08:36,193
- You could be magnificent.
- I'm required to kill, so I kill.

579
01:08:36,276 --> 01:08:38,195
That is enough.

580
01:08:38,278 --> 01:08:41,656
That's enough for the provinces,
but not for Rome.

581
01:08:44,117 --> 01:08:46,411
- The young emperor...

582
01:08:46,494 --> 01:08:49,456
has arranged
a series of spectacles...

583
01:08:49,497 --> 01:08:53,919
to commemorate his father,
Marcus Aurelius.

584
01:08:54,002 --> 01:08:55,962
I find that amusing...

585
01:08:56,046 --> 01:08:58,006
since it was Marcus Aurelius-

586
01:08:58,048 --> 01:09:00,842
the wise, the all-knowing
Marcus Aurelius-

587
01:09:00,884 --> 01:09:03,136
- that closed us down.

588
01:09:05,722 --> 01:09:09,684
So, finally, after five years
of scratching a living...

589
01:09:09,768 --> 01:09:12,354
in flea-infested
villages,

590
01:09:12,395 --> 01:09:15,732
we're finally going back
to where we belong-

591
01:09:15,774 --> 01:09:17,901
the Colosseum.

592
01:09:17,984 --> 01:09:22,405
Oh, you should see
the Colosseum, Spaniard.

593
01:09:23,698 --> 01:09:27,035
Fifty-thousand Romans...

594
01:09:27,077 --> 01:09:31,081
watching...
every movement of your sword,

595
01:09:31,164 --> 01:09:34,501
willing you to make
that killer blow.

596
01:09:35,752 --> 01:09:38,296
The silence before you strike...

597
01:09:38,380 --> 01:09:40,423
and the noise afterwards,

598
01:09:40,465 --> 01:09:43,510
it rises-
it rises up like-

599
01:09:43,593 --> 01:09:47,681
Like th-
Like- Like a storm...

600
01:09:47,764 --> 01:09:49,766
as if you were
the thunder god himself.

601
01:09:49,850 --> 01:09:53,895
- You were a gladiator?
- Yes, I was.

602
01:10:00,026 --> 01:10:01,987
You won your freedom?

603
01:10:02,028 --> 01:10:05,657
A long time ago,
the emperor...

604
01:10:05,699 --> 01:10:08,243
presented me
with a rudius.

605
01:10:08,326 --> 01:10:11,162
It's just a wooden sword.

606
01:10:12,706 --> 01:10:16,835
The symbol of your freedom.
He-

607
01:10:16,918 --> 01:10:21,506
- He touched me on the shoulder,
and I was free.

608
01:10:21,548 --> 01:10:25,385
- You knew Marcus Aurelius?
- I did not say I knew him.

609
01:10:25,427 --> 01:10:27,637
I said he touched me
on the shoulder once.

610
01:10:29,014 --> 01:10:32,392
You asked me what I want.

611
01:10:32,434 --> 01:10:35,020
I, too, want to stand
in front of the emperor...

612
01:10:36,313 --> 01:10:38,231
as you did.

613
01:10:38,315 --> 01:10:42,152
Then, listen to me.
Learn from me.

614
01:10:42,235 --> 01:10:46,406
I wasn't the best
because I killed quickly.

615
01:10:46,489 --> 01:10:50,076
I was the best
because the crowd loved me.

616
01:10:50,160 --> 01:10:55,248
Win the crowd,
and you'll win your freedom.

617
01:10:58,001 --> 01:11:00,378
I will win the crowd.

618
01:11:02,088 --> 01:11:06,593
- I will give them something
they have never seen before.
- Ha!

619
01:11:06,635 --> 01:11:10,347
So, Spaniard,
we shall go to Rome together...

620
01:11:10,430 --> 01:11:12,432
and have bloody adventures!

621
01:11:12,516 --> 01:11:14,601
And the great whore
will suckle us until we are...

622
01:11:14,684 --> 01:11:16,811
fat and happy and
can suckle no more.

623
01:11:16,895 --> 01:11:19,397
And then,

624
01:11:19,481 --> 01:11:23,235
when enough men have died,

625
01:11:23,318 --> 01:11:25,278
perhaps you will
have your freedom.

626
01:11:30,825 --> 01:11:33,578
Here. Use this.

627
01:11:55,600 --> 01:11:57,811
It's somewhere out there-

628
01:11:57,894 --> 01:12:02,732
my country, my home.

629
01:12:02,774 --> 01:12:06,570
My wife is preparing food.

630
01:12:06,611 --> 01:12:10,073
My daughters carry
water from the river.

631
01:12:10,115 --> 01:12:12,450
Will I ever
see them again?

632
01:12:12,492 --> 01:12:14,578
I think no.

633
01:12:14,661 --> 01:12:17,622
Do you believe you'll see
them again when you die?

634
01:12:17,706 --> 01:12:20,208
I think so.

635
01:12:20,292 --> 01:12:24,671
But then, I will die soon.

636
01:12:24,754 --> 01:12:26,673
They will not die
for many years.

637
01:12:28,383 --> 01:12:32,429
- I'll have to wait.
- But you would... wait.

638
01:12:32,512 --> 01:12:36,141
Of course.

639
01:12:36,224 --> 01:12:38,643
You see,

640
01:12:38,685 --> 01:12:43,523
my wife...
and my son...

641
01:12:43,565 --> 01:12:45,525
are already
waiting for me.

642
01:12:45,609 --> 01:12:48,111
You'll meet them again.

643
01:12:48,195 --> 01:12:51,364
But not yet.

644
01:12:54,242 --> 01:12:57,454
Not yet. Unless-

645
01:12:57,537 --> 01:12:59,456
Not yet.

646
01:13:02,542 --> 01:13:05,003
Not yet.

647
01:14:07,232 --> 01:14:09,860
Out!

648
01:14:09,943 --> 01:14:12,112
Go, go. Out!

649
01:14:24,374 --> 01:14:26,376
Good to see you again,
old friend.

650
01:14:31,715 --> 01:14:33,633
Bring me fortune.

651
01:14:38,388 --> 01:14:41,600
Have you ever seen
anything like that before?

652
01:14:41,641 --> 01:14:45,729
- I didn't know men
could build such things.

653
01:14:54,946 --> 01:14:56,865
Win the crowd.

654
01:14:56,948 --> 01:15:00,577
Get Inside! Move. Inside.

655
01:15:49,918 --> 01:15:53,004
He sleeps so well
because he's loved.

656
01:15:55,465 --> 01:15:59,594
Come, brother.
It's late.

657
01:16:01,221 --> 01:16:04,182
I will make Rome
the wonder of the ages.

658
01:16:06,518 --> 01:16:09,604
That is what Gracchus
and his friends don't understand.

659
01:16:09,688 --> 01:16:14,484
All my desires are splitting
my head to pieces.

660
01:16:20,949 --> 01:16:23,577
Commodus,
drink this tonic.

661
01:16:32,794 --> 01:16:36,423
I think the time
is almost right.

662
01:16:36,506 --> 01:16:38,633
I could announce
the dissolution of the Senate...

663
01:16:38,717 --> 01:16:40,635
at the celebration
to honor our father.

664
01:16:40,719 --> 01:16:43,847
You think I should?

665
01:16:43,889 --> 01:16:45,891
Are the people ready?

666
01:16:47,475 --> 01:16:49,436
I think you need
your rest now.

667
01:16:56,067 --> 01:16:59,779
- Will you stay with me?
- Still afraid of the dark, brother?

668
01:17:07,287 --> 01:17:13,126
Still. Always.

669
01:17:13,210 --> 01:17:16,129
- Stay with me tonight?
- You know I won't.

670
01:17:20,133 --> 01:17:22,052
Then, kiss me.

671
01:17:31,144 --> 01:17:33,855
Sleep, brother.

672
01:17:51,373 --> 01:17:53,750
Come on now.
Get out of the way!

673
01:17:58,547 --> 01:18:01,383
I want you. I want you.
I want you so-

674
01:18:01,466 --> 01:18:03,718
All right, Let him pass!

675
01:18:19,943 --> 01:18:22,279
-Sixty!

676
01:18:22,362 --> 01:18:25,907
-500!

677
01:18:25,949 --> 01:18:29,119
The emperor wants battles, and I don't
want to sacrifice my best fighters.

678
01:18:29,202 --> 01:18:32,747
The crowd wants battles,
so the emperor gives them battles.

679
01:18:32,789 --> 01:18:35,083
And you get
the battle of Carthage.

680
01:18:35,125 --> 01:18:38,628
The massacre of Carthage.
Guten tag.

681
01:18:38,712 --> 01:18:41,923
Oh, why don't you go down
to the prison and round up
all the beggars and thieves.

682
01:18:41,965 --> 01:18:43,925
We've done that.

683
01:18:44,009 --> 01:18:46,887
If you want to give away
the best gladiators
in the whole of the empire,

684
01:18:46,970 --> 01:18:49,431
I want double the rates.

685
01:18:49,514 --> 01:18:52,976
You'll get your contract rates,
or you'll get your contract cancelled.

686
01:18:53,059 --> 01:18:55,020
You don't like it?

687
01:18:55,061 --> 01:18:59,024
Then you can crawl back down
that shithole that you came from.

688
01:19:00,692 --> 01:19:03,612
-Cassius, please! Please, Cassius!

689
01:19:33,892 --> 01:19:36,520
Gladiator, are you the one
they call the Spaniard?

690
01:19:36,603 --> 01:19:40,607
- Yes.
- They said you were a giant.

691
01:19:40,690 --> 01:19:43,860
They said you could
crush a man's skull with one hand.

692
01:19:43,944 --> 01:19:47,197
A man's? No.

693
01:19:47,280 --> 01:19:50,075
A boy's.

694
01:19:51,535 --> 01:19:55,080
- They have good horses in Spain?
- Some of the best.

695
01:19:55,163 --> 01:19:59,543
This is Argento,
and this is Scarto.

696
01:19:59,626 --> 01:20:02,671
They were my horses.

697
01:20:02,754 --> 01:20:07,342
- They were taken from me.
- I like you, Spaniard.

698
01:20:07,425 --> 01:20:09,928
- I shall cheer for you.
- They let you watch the games?

699
01:20:10,011 --> 01:20:13,640
- My uncle says it makes me strong.
- And what does your father say?

700
01:20:13,723 --> 01:20:15,684
My father's dead.

701
01:20:17,310 --> 01:20:20,814
Master Lucius, it is time.

702
01:20:20,897 --> 01:20:24,526
- I have to go.
- Your name is Lucius?

703
01:20:26,236 --> 01:20:28,613
Lucius Verus,
after my father.

704
01:20:58,727 --> 01:21:00,896
Lower!

705
01:21:05,817 --> 01:21:09,738
-Claudius! More shields!
- Yes, sir.

706
01:21:30,050 --> 01:21:32,844
When the emperor enters,

707
01:21:32,928 --> 01:21:37,098
raise your weapons,
salute him and then speak together!

708
01:21:38,391 --> 01:21:42,395
Face the emperor and don't
turn your back on him!

709
01:21:42,479 --> 01:21:46,274
Go, and die with honor!

710
01:22:40,829 --> 01:22:43,456
Hail, mighty Caesar!

711
01:22:43,498 --> 01:22:47,460
Caesar! Caesar! Caesar!

712
01:22:47,544 --> 01:22:50,046
Caesar! Caesar! Caesar!

713
01:22:53,466 --> 01:22:56,136
And we who are about to die, salute you!

714
01:22:57,345 --> 01:23:00,390
On this day,

715
01:23:00,473 --> 01:23:04,352
we reach back
to hallowed antiquity...

716
01:23:04,394 --> 01:23:07,814
to bring you a recreation
of the second fall...

717
01:23:07,898 --> 01:23:09,941
of mighty Carthage!

718
01:23:14,070 --> 01:23:18,867
On the barren
plain of Zama,

719
01:23:18,950 --> 01:23:22,329
there stood
the invincible armies...

720
01:23:22,412 --> 01:23:25,582
of the barbarian, Hannibal.

721
01:23:25,624 --> 01:23:28,752
Ferocious mercenaries and warriors...

722
01:23:28,793 --> 01:23:31,463
from all brute nations...

723
01:23:31,546 --> 01:23:34,716
bent on merciless...

724
01:23:34,799 --> 01:23:38,512
destruction, conquest.

725
01:23:38,595 --> 01:23:42,641
Your emperor
is pleased to give you...

726
01:23:42,724 --> 01:23:45,477
the barbarian horde!

727
01:23:54,361 --> 01:23:57,614
- Anyone here been in the army?
- No.
- Yes.

728
01:23:57,697 --> 01:23:59,741
I served
with you at Vindobona.

729
01:23:59,824 --> 01:24:02,702
You can help me.

730
01:24:02,786 --> 01:24:06,456
Whatever comes
out of these gates,

731
01:24:06,540 --> 01:24:09,334
we've got a better chance
of survival if we work together.

732
01:24:10,710 --> 01:24:12,838
Do you understand?

733
01:24:13,880 --> 01:24:16,675
If we stay together,
we survive.

734
01:24:16,716 --> 01:24:19,344
I'm pleased to bring you
the legionnaires...

735
01:24:19,386 --> 01:24:24,057
of Scipio Africanus!

736
01:24:34,609 --> 01:24:37,070
To the death!

737
01:24:39,322 --> 01:24:44,244
- Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

738
01:24:46,121 --> 01:24:47,706
Stay close!

739
01:24:53,503 --> 01:24:55,755
Come together!

740
01:24:55,797 --> 01:24:58,383
- Staggered columns!

741
01:24:58,466 --> 01:25:00,677
Staggered columns!

742
01:25:12,647 --> 01:25:14,566
Soon all your men
will be slain.

743
01:25:14,649 --> 01:25:16,568
You don't have a chance!

744
01:25:27,662 --> 01:25:29,164
Lock your shields! Stay as one!

745
01:25:29,206 --> 01:25:31,208
As one! As one!

746
01:25:31,291 --> 01:25:32,876
Hold!

747
01:25:35,003 --> 01:25:36,588
Hold!

748
01:25:36,671 --> 01:25:38,757
- As one!
- As one!

749
01:25:41,092 --> 01:25:42,802
Well done!

750
01:25:45,847 --> 01:25:48,183
Hyah! Hyah!

751
01:25:54,314 --> 01:25:55,899
Hold!

752
01:25:55,982 --> 01:25:58,944
Diamond! Diamond!

753
01:26:03,615 --> 01:26:05,450
- Yes!

754
01:26:17,254 --> 01:26:19,130
- Haken!

755
01:26:42,612 --> 01:26:44,990
This column to the chariots!
This column...

756
01:26:45,031 --> 01:26:46,867
-stay with me!

757
01:26:49,786 --> 01:26:51,538
Quickly!

758
01:26:51,621 --> 01:26:54,374
- Get out there!
- Hurry!

759
01:27:35,832 --> 01:27:37,876
Maximus!

760
01:27:41,004 --> 01:27:42,255
Ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh.

761
01:27:48,345 --> 01:27:51,264
Single column!
Single column!

762
01:27:51,348 --> 01:27:52,974
Single column! Single column!

763
01:28:36,935 --> 01:28:39,604
- We win!

764
01:28:43,525 --> 01:28:46,945
My history's
a little hazy, Cassius.

765
01:28:46,987 --> 01:28:49,906
But shouldn't the barbarians
lose the battle of Carthage?

766
01:28:49,990 --> 01:28:52,325
Uh, yes, sire.

767
01:28:52,367 --> 01:28:54,661
Um, forgive me, sire.

768
01:28:54,703 --> 01:28:58,415
No, I rather
enjoy surprises.

769
01:28:58,498 --> 01:29:03,712
- Who is he?
- They call him the Spaniard, sire.

770
01:29:05,255 --> 01:29:09,676
- I think I'll meet him.
- Yes, sire.

771
01:29:09,759 --> 01:29:13,763
Hail to the barbarians!

772
01:29:27,861 --> 01:29:32,532
Forward! Arms at ready!

773
01:29:44,461 --> 01:29:46,713
Drop your weapons!

774
01:29:48,965 --> 01:29:53,595
Gladiator, the emperor
has asked for you.

775
01:29:53,637 --> 01:29:55,639
I'm at the emperor's service.

776
01:30:22,582 --> 01:30:26,753
Rise. Rise.

777
01:30:34,386 --> 01:30:36,596
Your fame is well deserved,
Spaniard.

778
01:30:36,680 --> 01:30:39,683
I don't think there's ever
been a gladiator to match you.

779
01:30:39,724 --> 01:30:42,269
As for this young man,
he insists you are Hector reborn.

780
01:30:42,352 --> 01:30:44,938
Or was it Hercules?

781
01:30:45,021 --> 01:30:48,859
Why doesn't the hero reveal himself
and tell us all your real name?

782
01:30:50,861 --> 01:30:55,699
- You do have a name?
- My name is Gladiator.

783
01:30:58,618 --> 01:31:01,121
- How dare you show your back to me?

784
01:31:01,204 --> 01:31:03,623
Slave!

785
01:31:03,707 --> 01:31:05,750
You will remove your helmet
and tell me your name.

786
01:31:17,679 --> 01:31:20,599
My name is
Maximus Decimus Meridius,

787
01:31:20,640 --> 01:31:23,018
commander of the armies
of the north,

788
01:31:23,101 --> 01:31:25,854
general of the Felix Legions,

789
01:31:25,937 --> 01:31:30,358
Loyal servant to the true emperor,
Marcus Aurelius,

790
01:31:30,442 --> 01:31:32,903
father to a murdered son,

791
01:31:32,986 --> 01:31:35,780
husband to a murdered wife...

792
01:31:35,864 --> 01:31:39,451
and I will have my vengeance...
in this life or the next.

793
01:31:46,041 --> 01:31:49,169
Arms!

794
01:32:00,305 --> 01:32:04,809
Live! Live! Live!
Live! Live! Live!

795
01:32:04,893 --> 01:32:10,565
Live! Live! Live!
Live! Live! Live!

796
01:32:12,651 --> 01:32:15,320
Live! Live! Live!

797
01:32:15,403 --> 01:32:18,907
Live! Live!
Live! Live!

798
01:32:51,606 --> 01:32:55,151
Guards, at rest!

799
01:33:44,367 --> 01:33:48,997
Maximus! Maximus!
Maximus! Maximus!

800
01:33:49,080 --> 01:33:52,292
Maximus! Maximus! Maximus!

801
01:33:52,375 --> 01:33:55,378
Maximus! Maximus! Maximus!

802
01:34:15,690 --> 01:34:18,902
Why is he still alive?

803
01:34:18,985 --> 01:34:21,112
I don't know.

804
01:34:21,196 --> 01:34:23,448
He shouldn't be alive.

805
01:34:23,532 --> 01:34:26,368
It vexes me.

806
01:34:26,409 --> 01:34:29,371
I'm terribly vexed.

807
01:34:39,339 --> 01:34:41,258
I did what I had to do.

808
01:34:41,341 --> 01:34:46,221
If Father had had his way,
the empire would have been torn apart.

809
01:34:46,263 --> 01:34:48,515
You do see that?

810
01:34:48,598 --> 01:34:50,517
Yes.

811
01:34:54,229 --> 01:34:57,649
What did you feel...
when you saw him?

812
01:34:59,901 --> 01:35:02,779
I felt nothing.

813
01:35:02,821 --> 01:35:05,824
He wounded you deeply,
didn't he?

814
01:35:06,950 --> 01:35:10,328
No more than
I wounded him.

815
01:35:13,832 --> 01:35:16,168
They lied to me in Germania.

816
01:35:17,419 --> 01:35:20,255
They told me he was dead.

817
01:35:21,548 --> 01:35:24,467
If they lie to me,
they don't respect me.

818
01:35:24,509 --> 01:35:27,220
If they don't respect me,
how can they ever love me?

819
01:35:29,097 --> 01:35:31,808
Then you must
let the legions know...

820
01:35:31,892 --> 01:35:35,437
their treachery
will not go unpunished.

821
01:35:35,520 --> 01:35:39,900
Poor sister, I wouldn't
want to be your enemy.

822
01:35:41,026 --> 01:35:43,361
What will you do?

823
01:35:54,581 --> 01:35:56,500
This way!

824
01:36:30,910 --> 01:36:34,080
Rich matrons pay well to be pleasured
by the bravest champions.

825
01:36:34,164 --> 01:36:37,167
I knew your brother
would send assassins.

826
01:36:37,250 --> 01:36:39,961
I didn't realize
he would send his best.

827
01:36:41,463 --> 01:36:44,382
Maximus,
he doesn't know.

828
01:36:44,424 --> 01:36:47,385
My family was burned and crucified
while they were still alive.

829
01:36:47,427 --> 01:36:50,388
- I knew nothing-
- Don't lie to me!

830
01:36:56,936 --> 01:37:00,190
- I wept for them.
- As you wept for your father?

831
01:37:00,231 --> 01:37:02,942
As you wept for
your father?

832
01:37:03,026 --> 01:37:06,696
I have been living in
a prison of fear since that day.

833
01:37:06,738 --> 01:37:11,409
To be unable to mourn your father
for fear of your brother.

834
01:37:11,451 --> 01:37:14,412
To live in terror
every moment of every day...

835
01:37:14,454 --> 01:37:16,748
because your son
is heir to the throne.

836
01:37:18,833 --> 01:37:22,045
Oh, I have wept.

837
01:37:22,128 --> 01:37:25,298
My son was innocent.

838
01:37:25,382 --> 01:37:28,051
So is mine.

839
01:37:29,552 --> 01:37:32,472
Must my son die, too,
before you will trust me?

840
01:37:34,516 --> 01:37:38,311
What does it matter
if I trust you or not?

841
01:37:38,395 --> 01:37:41,272
The gods have spared you.
Don't you understand?

842
01:37:41,314 --> 01:37:44,818
Today I saw a slave become
more powerful than the emperor of Rome.

843
01:37:44,901 --> 01:37:46,945
The gods
have spared me?

844
01:37:47,028 --> 01:37:50,407
I am at their mercy,
with the power only to amuse a mob!

845
01:37:50,490 --> 01:37:53,660
That is power.
The mob is Rome.

846
01:37:53,702 --> 01:37:56,454
And while Commodus controls them,
he controls everything.

847
01:37:57,747 --> 01:37:59,708
Listen to me.

848
01:37:59,791 --> 01:38:03,003
My brother has enemies,
most of all in the senate.

849
01:38:03,044 --> 01:38:05,505
But while
the people follow him,

850
01:38:05,547 --> 01:38:08,675
no one would dare
stand up to him until you.

851
01:38:08,758 --> 01:38:11,761
They oppose him,
yet they do nothing.

852
01:38:11,845 --> 01:38:15,557
There are some politicians
who have dedicated their lives to Rome.

853
01:38:15,598 --> 01:38:18,309
One man above all.

854
01:38:18,393 --> 01:38:21,604
If I can arrange it,
will you meet him?

855
01:38:21,688 --> 01:38:23,940
Do you not understand?

856
01:38:24,024 --> 01:38:28,236
I may die in this cell tonight,
or in the arena tomorrow. I am a slave!

857
01:38:28,278 --> 01:38:30,739
What possible
difference can I make?

858
01:38:30,780 --> 01:38:33,408
This man wants
what you want.

859
01:38:33,450 --> 01:38:36,453
Then have him
kill Commodus!

860
01:38:38,371 --> 01:38:41,082
I knew a man once,

861
01:38:41,124 --> 01:38:44,502
a noble man,
a man of principle...

862
01:38:44,586 --> 01:38:47,297
who loved
my father.

863
01:38:47,380 --> 01:38:50,175
And my father
loved him.

864
01:38:51,301 --> 01:38:53,887
This man
served Rome well.

865
01:38:57,807 --> 01:39:00,060
That man is gone.

866
01:39:00,143 --> 01:39:02,395
Your brother
did his work well.

867
01:39:02,479 --> 01:39:04,898
Let me help you.

868
01:39:10,445 --> 01:39:14,157
Yes, you can help me.

869
01:39:16,826 --> 01:39:18,953
Forget you ever knew me...

870
01:39:19,037 --> 01:39:21,122
and never
come here again.

871
01:39:24,209 --> 01:39:27,629
Guard! The lady has finished with me.

872
01:39:55,240 --> 01:39:57,158
Maximus?

873
01:39:57,242 --> 01:40:00,912
You commanded legions?
You had many victories?

874
01:40:00,954 --> 01:40:03,957
- Yes.
- In Germania?

875
01:40:05,709 --> 01:40:08,294
In many countries.

876
01:40:09,379 --> 01:40:11,965
General.

877
01:40:59,471 --> 01:41:02,015
You have a great name.

878
01:41:02,098 --> 01:41:05,060
He must kill your name
before he kills you.

879
01:41:14,486 --> 01:41:16,446
Yes, at the far end.

880
01:41:16,488 --> 01:41:18,948
- Senator Gaius.
- Hello.

881
01:41:18,990 --> 01:41:20,950
Senator Gracchus.

882
01:41:22,494 --> 01:41:25,872
Don't often see you enjoying
the pleasures of the vulgar crowd.

883
01:41:25,955 --> 01:41:28,541
I don't pretend to be a man
of the people, Senator.

884
01:41:28,625 --> 01:41:31,711
But I do try to be a man
for the people.

885
01:41:45,684 --> 01:41:49,354
Caesar! Caesar! Caesar!

886
01:41:49,437 --> 01:41:51,398
Caesar! Caesar!

887
01:41:51,439 --> 01:41:55,193
Caesar! Caesar! Caesar!

888
01:41:57,404 --> 01:41:59,656
People of Rome!

889
01:42:01,741 --> 01:42:04,577
On the fourth day
of Antioch,

890
01:42:04,661 --> 01:42:08,581
we can celebrate
the 64th day of the games.

891
01:42:09,749 --> 01:42:14,671
And, in his
majestic charity,

892
01:42:14,754 --> 01:42:19,384
the Emperor has deigned this day
to favor the people of Rome...

893
01:42:19,467 --> 01:42:23,638
with an historical
final match.

894
01:42:23,722 --> 01:42:25,974
Returning to the Colosseum today...

895
01:42:26,057 --> 01:42:30,520
after five years
in retirement, Caesar...

896
01:42:30,603 --> 01:42:34,482
is pleased to bring you
the only...

897
01:42:34,524 --> 01:42:36,818
undefeated champion...

898
01:42:36,901 --> 01:42:39,320
- Yah! Yah!
-in Roman history,

899
01:42:39,404 --> 01:42:44,617
the legendary Tigris of Gaul!

900
01:42:59,716 --> 01:43:01,926
Whoa! Whoa!

901
01:43:05,722 --> 01:43:09,225
He knows too well
how to manipulate the mob.

902
01:43:09,309 --> 01:43:12,020
Marcus Aurelius had a dream
that was Rome, Proximo.

903
01:43:12,103 --> 01:43:14,564
This is not it!
This is not it!

904
01:43:14,606 --> 01:43:17,233
Marcus Aurelius is dead,
Maximus.

905
01:43:17,317 --> 01:43:20,528
We mortals are but
shadows and dust.

906
01:43:20,570 --> 01:43:23,990
- Shadows and dust, Maximus!

907
01:43:24,074 --> 01:43:27,410
Representing the training
lyceum of Antonius Proximo,

908
01:43:27,494 --> 01:43:31,331
Caesar is proud
to give you...

909
01:43:31,414 --> 01:43:34,709
Aelius Maximus!

910
01:43:40,799 --> 01:43:45,261
Maximus! Maximus! Maximus!

911
01:43:45,345 --> 01:43:48,098
Maximus! Maximus!

912
01:43:48,181 --> 01:43:50,433
They embrace him like
he's one of their own.

913
01:43:50,475 --> 01:43:54,187
The mob is fickle, brother.
He'll be forgotten in a month.

914
01:43:54,270 --> 01:43:57,107
Maximus! Maximus!

915
01:43:57,148 --> 01:44:00,193
No, much sooner
than that.

916
01:44:01,986 --> 01:44:04,531
It's been arranged.

917
01:44:10,245 --> 01:44:13,373
Maximus! Maximus! Maximus!

918
01:44:22,215 --> 01:44:24,926
We who are about to die salute you.

919
01:44:28,555 --> 01:44:31,099
We're with you, Maximus!

920
01:45:12,640 --> 01:45:15,393
Come on, finish it!

921
01:45:41,169 --> 01:45:43,755
- No!
- Pull! Pull!

922
01:45:57,519 --> 01:46:00,230
- Aah!

923
01:46:05,819 --> 01:46:07,696
Yeah!

924
01:46:16,955 --> 01:46:19,457
Loose! Loose!
Loose! Loose!

925
01:46:34,014 --> 01:46:37,058
Aah!

926
01:46:40,020 --> 01:46:42,647
Aah!

927
01:46:46,860 --> 01:46:48,737
Get him!
Kill him!

928
01:46:48,820 --> 01:46:52,324
Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill!

929
01:46:52,407 --> 01:46:55,368
Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill!

930
01:46:55,410 --> 01:46:58,496
Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill!

931
01:46:58,580 --> 01:47:01,666
Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill!

932
01:47:01,750 --> 01:47:04,753
Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill!

933
01:47:04,836 --> 01:47:09,049
Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill!

934
01:47:09,090 --> 01:47:12,093
Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill!

935
01:47:12,135 --> 01:47:15,013
- Kill! Kill!
- Kill! Kill!

936
01:47:15,096 --> 01:47:17,599
- Kill!
- Kill!

937
01:47:17,682 --> 01:47:20,643
Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill!

938
01:47:20,727 --> 01:47:24,773
Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill!

939
01:47:24,856 --> 01:47:28,360
Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill!

940
01:47:28,443 --> 01:47:32,113
Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill!

941
01:47:32,197 --> 01:47:35,200
Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill!

942
01:47:35,283 --> 01:47:38,995
Kill! Kill!
Kill! Kill!

943
01:47:52,884 --> 01:47:55,970
Maximus!
Maximus the Merciful!

944
01:47:56,054 --> 01:47:59,099
Maximus the Merciful!

945
01:48:03,645 --> 01:48:05,939
Maximus the Merciful!

946
01:48:06,022 --> 01:48:07,982
Maximus! Maximus!

947
01:48:08,024 --> 01:48:10,360
Maximus! Maximus!

948
01:48:10,402 --> 01:48:14,698
Maximus! Maximus!
Maximus!

949
01:48:14,739 --> 01:48:17,367
Maximus! Maximus!
Maximus!

950
01:48:17,575 --> 01:48:21,204
Forward, guards! On battery!

951
01:48:21,246 --> 01:48:23,248
Maximus! Maximus!

952
01:48:26,209 --> 01:48:29,796
Maximus! Maximus! Maximus!

953
01:48:29,879 --> 01:48:32,215
Maximus!
Maximus!

954
01:48:50,483 --> 01:48:54,821
What am I going
to do with you?

955
01:48:54,904 --> 01:48:57,490
You simply won't...

956
01:48:57,574 --> 01:48:59,492
die.

957
01:49:03,121 --> 01:49:06,499
Are we so different,
you and l?

958
01:49:06,541 --> 01:49:08,543
You take life
when you have to...

959
01:49:08,626 --> 01:49:10,628
as I do.

960
01:49:10,712 --> 01:49:14,758
I have only one more life to take.
Then it is done.

961
01:49:14,841 --> 01:49:17,135
Then take it now.

962
01:49:29,898 --> 01:49:32,525
They tell me your son...

963
01:49:32,567 --> 01:49:34,903
squealed like a girl...

964
01:49:34,986 --> 01:49:37,822
when they nailed him
to the cross.

965
01:49:37,906 --> 01:49:42,535
And your wife...
moaned like a whore...

966
01:49:44,663 --> 01:49:46,790
when they ravaged her...

967
01:49:46,873 --> 01:49:49,167
again and again...

968
01:49:50,543 --> 01:49:52,462
and again.

969
01:49:57,258 --> 01:50:00,929
The time for honoring yourself
will soon be at an end.

970
01:50:05,809 --> 01:50:07,936
Highness.

971
01:50:19,406 --> 01:50:23,451
Maximus! Maximus! Maximus!

972
01:50:23,493 --> 01:50:26,913
Maximus! Maximus! Maximus!

973
01:50:26,997 --> 01:50:31,960
Maximus! Maximus!
Maximus! Maximus!

974
01:50:33,962 --> 01:50:37,507
General! General!

975
01:50:37,590 --> 01:50:39,467
General!

976
01:50:39,551 --> 01:50:42,220
- General! General!
- Get back!

977
01:50:42,303 --> 01:50:44,806
- General!
- Cicero!

978
01:50:44,889 --> 01:50:47,851
Maximus! Maximus!

979
01:50:47,934 --> 01:50:50,145
- General!

980
01:50:50,228 --> 01:50:52,814
- General.
- Where are you camped?

981
01:50:52,897 --> 01:50:56,443
- Ostia.
- Maximus! Maximus!

982
01:50:56,526 --> 01:51:00,739
Maximus! Maximus!
Maximus! Maximus!

983
01:51:00,780 --> 01:51:03,616
- We love you, Maximus!
- Praise the victor!

984
01:51:03,700 --> 01:51:06,411
Tell the men their general lives.
Find me.

985
01:51:06,453 --> 01:51:09,581
- Move along!
- Find me!

986
01:51:09,664 --> 01:51:14,336
Maximus! Maximus!
Maximus! Maximus!

987
01:51:33,730 --> 01:51:36,149
Can they hear you?

988
01:51:39,194 --> 01:51:41,112
Who?

989
01:51:41,196 --> 01:51:44,199
Your family,
in the afterlife.

990
01:51:45,700 --> 01:51:48,119
- Oh, yes.
- What do you say to them?

991
01:51:52,040 --> 01:51:54,334
To my boy,

992
01:51:54,376 --> 01:51:56,628
I tell him I will
see him again soon.

993
01:51:56,711 --> 01:52:01,216
To keep his heels down
when he's riding his horse.

994
01:52:02,884 --> 01:52:04,803
To my wife-

995
01:52:06,721 --> 01:52:09,015
That is not
your business.

996
01:52:16,356 --> 01:52:19,401
And now they love Maximus
for his mercy.

997
01:52:20,944 --> 01:52:24,197
So I can't just kill him,
or it makes me even more unmerciful!

998
01:52:25,824 --> 01:52:30,245
The whole thing's
like some crazed nightmare.

999
01:52:31,287 --> 01:52:33,748
He is defying you.

1000
01:52:33,790 --> 01:52:36,793
His every victory
is an act of defiance.

1001
01:52:36,835 --> 01:52:40,922
The mob sees this,
and so do the senate.

1002
01:52:40,964 --> 01:52:45,427
Every day he lives,
they grow bolder.

1003
01:52:45,468 --> 01:52:47,595
- Kill him.
- No.

1004
01:52:49,180 --> 01:52:51,766
I will not make
a martyr of him.

1005
01:52:57,355 --> 01:52:59,524
I have been told...

1006
01:52:59,607 --> 01:53:01,526
of a certain sea snake...

1007
01:53:01,609 --> 01:53:05,947
which has a very unusual method
of attracting its prey.

1008
01:53:06,031 --> 01:53:10,702
It will lie at the bottom
of the ocean as if wounded.

1009
01:53:10,785 --> 01:53:13,038
Then its enemies
will approach,

1010
01:53:13,121 --> 01:53:16,041
and yet it will
lie quite still.

1011
01:53:16,124 --> 01:53:20,420
And then its enemies
will take little bites of it,

1012
01:53:20,503 --> 01:53:22,797
and yet it remains...

1013
01:53:22,881 --> 01:53:25,508
still.

1014
01:53:27,052 --> 01:53:29,346
So,

1015
01:53:29,429 --> 01:53:31,973
we will lie still...

1016
01:53:32,057 --> 01:53:35,602
and let our enemies
come to us and nibble.

1017
01:53:35,685 --> 01:53:39,105
Have every senator followed.

1018
01:53:52,160 --> 01:53:54,120
Maximus.

1019
01:53:55,664 --> 01:53:57,624
Cicero, my old friend.

1020
01:53:57,666 --> 01:53:59,709
I thought perhaps
I'd seen you for the last time.

1021
01:53:59,793 --> 01:54:02,045
- I thought you were dead.
- Close.

1022
01:54:02,128 --> 01:54:04,464
How long have the men
been in Ostia?

1023
01:54:04,547 --> 01:54:07,509
- All winter.
- And how do they look?

1024
01:54:07,592 --> 01:54:09,803
Fattened and bored.

1025
01:54:09,886 --> 01:54:11,846
Who's in command?

1026
01:54:11,888 --> 01:54:14,849
Some fool from Rome.

1027
01:54:14,891 --> 01:54:18,353
- How soon do you think they
could be ready to fight?
- For you, tomorrow.

1028
01:54:20,021 --> 01:54:22,649
I need you to
do something for me.

1029
01:54:26,987 --> 01:54:28,905
Come see. Witness.

1030
01:54:28,989 --> 01:54:31,825
If you haven't been in the arena,
you can see the show here.

1031
01:54:31,908 --> 01:54:36,371
Giant Maximus is defeating
our Emperor Commodus. What are we to do?

1032
01:54:36,454 --> 01:54:39,207
He's defying everyone.
What will we do?

1033
01:54:39,249 --> 01:54:42,002
- Ah! Look at that!

1034
01:54:42,085 --> 01:54:44,546
- Oh, he got him!

1035
01:54:44,587 --> 01:54:47,215
Give way! Give way!

1036
01:54:47,257 --> 01:54:49,384
Give way!

1037
01:54:51,261 --> 01:54:53,888
Three casks of red wine.

1038
01:54:53,972 --> 01:54:56,516
My lady?
I served your father at Vindobona.

1039
01:54:56,599 --> 01:54:58,518
-Back.
- Mylady.

1040
01:54:58,601 --> 01:55:00,562
I served your father
at Vindobona.

1041
01:55:00,645 --> 01:55:03,398
- Back!
- And I served the General Maximus.

1042
01:55:03,481 --> 01:55:05,734
I serve him still.

1043
01:55:05,817 --> 01:55:07,736
Stop.

1044
01:55:07,819 --> 01:55:09,946
- Stop.
-Stop!

1045
01:55:11,031 --> 01:55:13,283
Stand back.

1046
01:55:13,366 --> 01:55:16,119
The General sends word.
He will meet your politician.

1047
01:55:18,288 --> 01:55:22,459
- For your loyalty, soldier.
- Thank you, my lady.

1048
01:55:22,542 --> 01:55:24,919
Hup!

1049
01:55:31,343 --> 01:55:33,803
Leave us.

1050
01:55:38,433 --> 01:55:40,352
Senator Gracchus.

1051
01:55:53,907 --> 01:55:56,201
General.

1052
01:55:56,242 --> 01:56:00,288
I hope my coming here today
is evidence enough that...

1053
01:56:00,372 --> 01:56:02,290
you can trust me.

1054
01:56:06,044 --> 01:56:08,546
- The senate is with you?
- The senate?

1055
01:56:10,590 --> 01:56:13,885
Yes. I can speak for them.

1056
01:56:13,927 --> 01:56:17,430
You can buy my freedom
and smuggle me out of Rome?

1057
01:56:17,514 --> 01:56:20,433
To what end?

1058
01:56:20,475 --> 01:56:23,269
Get me outside
the city walls.

1059
01:56:23,311 --> 01:56:27,315
Have fresh horses ready to take me
to Ostia. My army's encamped there.

1060
01:56:27,399 --> 01:56:30,986
By nightfall of the second day,
I shall return at the head of 5,000 men.

1061
01:56:31,069 --> 01:56:34,614
But the legions all have new commanders
loyal to Commodus.

1062
01:56:34,698 --> 01:56:37,951
Let my men see me alive, and you
shall see where their loyalties lie.

1063
01:56:37,993 --> 01:56:40,120
This is madness.

1064
01:56:40,203 --> 01:56:43,665
- No Roman army has entered
the capital in a hundred years.
- Gracchus-

1065
01:56:43,707 --> 01:56:45,625
I will not trade
one dictatorship for another!

1066
01:56:45,667 --> 01:56:50,505
The time for half-measures
and talk is over, Senator.

1067
01:56:50,588 --> 01:56:54,092
And after your glorious coup,
what then?

1068
01:56:54,175 --> 01:56:57,637
You'll take your
5,000 warriors and leave?

1069
01:56:57,721 --> 01:57:00,056
I will leave.

1070
01:57:00,140 --> 01:57:03,852
The soldiers will stay
for your protection,
under the command of the senate.

1071
01:57:03,935 --> 01:57:07,313
So, once all
of Rome is yours,

1072
01:57:07,397 --> 01:57:10,358
you'll just give it
back to the people?

1073
01:57:10,442 --> 01:57:12,402
Tell me why.

1074
01:57:18,158 --> 01:57:20,618
Because that was the
last wish of a dying man.

1075
01:57:24,372 --> 01:57:26,291
I will kill Commodus.

1076
01:57:28,168 --> 01:57:31,629
The fate of Rome
I leave to you.

1077
01:57:33,131 --> 01:57:35,717
Marcus Aurelius trusted you.

1078
01:57:37,218 --> 01:57:39,637
His daughter trusts you.

1079
01:57:43,183 --> 01:57:45,268
I will trust you.

1080
01:57:45,352 --> 01:57:47,854
But we have little time.

1081
01:57:47,937 --> 01:57:50,023
Give me two days...

1082
01:57:50,106 --> 01:57:53,318
and I will buy your freedom.

1083
01:57:53,401 --> 01:57:56,154
And you-

1084
01:57:56,237 --> 01:57:58,990
You stay alive.

1085
01:57:59,074 --> 01:58:01,409
Or I'll be dead.

1086
01:58:02,619 --> 01:58:04,621
Now we must go.

1087
01:58:09,793 --> 01:58:12,212
It won't work.

1088
01:58:12,253 --> 01:58:15,340
The Emperor
knows too much.

1089
01:58:15,382 --> 01:58:17,384
And as for me,

1090
01:58:18,551 --> 01:58:21,721
it's becoming dangerous.

1091
01:58:21,805 --> 01:58:24,265
You will be paid
on my return.

1092
01:58:26,059 --> 01:58:28,186
- I give you my word.

1093
01:58:28,228 --> 01:58:30,939
Your word?
What if you don't return?

1094
01:58:31,022 --> 01:58:34,442
Do you remember what it was
to have trust, Proximo?

1095
01:58:34,526 --> 01:58:37,070
Trust?

1096
01:58:40,532 --> 01:58:42,450
Who am I to trust?

1097
01:58:42,534 --> 01:58:45,245
I will kill Commodus.

1098
01:58:45,286 --> 01:58:47,288
Why would I want that?

1099
01:58:47,372 --> 01:58:49,290
He makes me rich.

1100
01:58:51,876 --> 01:58:54,087
Oh, l-

1101
01:58:54,129 --> 01:58:57,424
I know that you are
a man of your word, General.

1102
01:58:58,800 --> 01:59:01,428
I know that you
would die for honor.

1103
01:59:02,929 --> 01:59:05,473
You would
die for Rome.

1104
01:59:05,557 --> 01:59:07,976
You would die for
the memory of your ancestors.

1105
01:59:08,059 --> 01:59:10,854
But l,
on the other hand-

1106
01:59:14,024 --> 01:59:15,942
I'm an entertainer.

1107
01:59:17,986 --> 01:59:20,405
Hmm? Guard!

1108
01:59:24,909 --> 01:59:27,370
He killed the man
who set you free.

1109
01:59:33,629 --> 01:59:36,049
Praetorians, master.

1110
01:59:42,096 --> 01:59:44,057
Halt!

1111
01:59:53,983 --> 01:59:56,069
Where have you been?

1112
01:59:56,152 --> 01:59:58,112
I sent for you.

1113
01:59:59,280 --> 02:00:01,240
Please, brother.

1114
02:00:05,787 --> 02:00:07,705
What's troubling you?

1115
02:00:10,958 --> 02:00:13,419
Does Gracchus
have a new lover?

1116
02:00:15,171 --> 02:00:17,090
I don't know.

1117
02:00:18,341 --> 02:00:20,259
I thought you'd seen him.

1118
02:00:21,678 --> 02:00:24,430
He infects everyone
like a putrid fever.

1119
02:00:25,682 --> 02:00:27,975
For the health of Rome,
the senate must be bled.

1120
02:00:29,477 --> 02:00:31,396
And he will bleed, too.

1121
02:00:31,479 --> 02:00:34,190
Very soon.

1122
02:00:35,400 --> 02:00:37,568
But not tonight.

1123
02:00:51,499 --> 02:00:53,918
Do you remember what
our father said once?

1124
02:00:56,170 --> 02:00:58,089
"It's a dream-

1125
02:00:59,924 --> 02:01:02,468
a frightful dream-

1126
02:01:04,387 --> 02:01:06,556
Life is."

1127
02:01:08,349 --> 02:01:10,601
Do you think that's true?

1128
02:01:10,685 --> 02:01:13,229
I don't know.

1129
02:01:16,190 --> 02:01:18,109
I think it is.

1130
02:01:20,653 --> 02:01:23,323
And I have only you
to share it with.

1131
02:02:01,110 --> 02:02:03,154
Open your mouth.

1132
02:02:39,482 --> 02:02:41,609
You know I love you.

1133
02:02:43,736 --> 02:02:45,989
And I love you.

1134
02:03:21,691 --> 02:03:24,110
Out. Get out!

1135
02:03:24,193 --> 02:03:26,571
Move!

1136
02:03:30,700 --> 02:03:32,744
Congratulations, General.

1137
02:03:32,827 --> 02:03:36,289
You've got very...
persuasive friends.

1138
02:03:41,627 --> 02:03:44,130
My brother's had
Gracchus arrested.

1139
02:03:44,213 --> 02:03:48,217
We daren't wait any longer.
We must leave tonight.

1140
02:03:48,301 --> 02:03:52,013
Proximo will come at midnight
and take you to the gate.

1141
02:03:52,096 --> 02:03:54,891
Your servant, Cicero,
will be waiting there with horses.

1142
02:03:57,643 --> 02:03:59,604
You have done all this?

1143
02:03:59,645 --> 02:04:02,523
- Yes.
- You risk too much.

1144
02:04:03,941 --> 02:04:06,361
I have much to pay for.

1145
02:04:08,112 --> 02:04:10,031
You have nothing to pay for.

1146
02:04:10,114 --> 02:04:13,701
You love your son.
You're strong for him.

1147
02:04:16,871 --> 02:04:20,583
I am tired of being strong.

1148
02:04:20,667 --> 02:04:23,419
My brother hates all the world,

1149
02:04:23,503 --> 02:04:25,421
and you most of all.

1150
02:04:25,505 --> 02:04:29,384
- Because your father chose me.
- No.

1151
02:04:30,468 --> 02:04:33,012
Because my father loved you.

1152
02:04:36,557 --> 02:04:39,394
And because I loved you.

1153
02:04:41,562 --> 02:04:43,523
A long time ago.

1154
02:04:47,610 --> 02:04:49,904
Was I very different then?

1155
02:04:56,619 --> 02:04:58,538
You laughed more.

1156
02:05:02,458 --> 02:05:06,087
I have felt alone
all my life,

1157
02:05:06,170 --> 02:05:08,256
except with you.

1158
02:05:10,967 --> 02:05:12,885
I must go.

1159
02:05:12,969 --> 02:05:15,555
Yes.

1160
02:05:42,165 --> 02:05:44,292
There. There.

1161
02:05:44,375 --> 02:05:47,795
- There. There. There.
There. There. There.

1162
02:05:47,879 --> 02:05:50,006
There. There. There.

1163
02:05:50,089 --> 02:05:52,175
There. There. There.

1164
02:05:52,258 --> 02:05:54,761
- There. There. There. There.

1165
02:05:54,844 --> 02:05:56,763
And I've got you.

1166
02:05:59,432 --> 02:06:01,893
Isn't it late
to be playing legionnaire?

1167
02:06:01,934 --> 02:06:04,312
I'm not a legionnaire.

1168
02:06:04,395 --> 02:06:06,564
- Not a legionnaire?
- I'm a gladiator.

1169
02:06:08,149 --> 02:06:12,028
A gladiator?
Gladiators only fight in the games.

1170
02:06:12,111 --> 02:06:14,197
Wouldn't you rather be...

1171
02:06:14,280 --> 02:06:16,449
a great Roman warrior
like Julius Caesar?

1172
02:06:16,532 --> 02:06:19,619
I'm Maximus,
the savior of Rome!

1173
02:06:21,245 --> 02:06:23,581
The savior of Rome?

1174
02:06:31,923 --> 02:06:33,841
And who said that?

1175
02:06:42,433 --> 02:06:44,852
Where's Lucius?

1176
02:06:44,894 --> 02:06:46,854
He's with the Emperor, my lady.

1177
02:06:50,692 --> 02:06:53,736
-She couldn't.
- Yes, she did.

1178
02:06:53,820 --> 02:06:57,407
She took it from a basket
and pressed it to her breast,

1179
02:06:57,490 --> 02:06:59,409
right here
above her heart.

1180
02:07:01,536 --> 02:07:03,788
It bit her in the breast?

1181
02:07:03,871 --> 02:07:05,790
Yes.

1182
02:07:05,873 --> 02:07:08,918
You see, Lucius,
sometimes royal ladies...

1183
02:07:09,002 --> 02:07:12,797
behave very strangely and do
very odd things in the name of love.

1184
02:07:12,880 --> 02:07:14,799
I think it's silly.

1185
02:07:14,882 --> 02:07:16,801
So do l.

1186
02:07:18,302 --> 02:07:20,263
So do l.

1187
02:07:20,304 --> 02:07:22,473
Sister, join us.

1188
02:07:22,557 --> 02:07:24,767
I've been reading
to dear Lucius.

1189
02:07:24,851 --> 02:07:27,562
- I've been reading too.
- Yes.

1190
02:07:27,603 --> 02:07:29,564
He's a very clever
little boy.

1191
02:07:29,605 --> 02:07:32,734
He'll make a grand
emperor one day.

1192
02:07:32,775 --> 02:07:36,487
We've been reading about the great
Mark Antony and his adventures in Egypt.

1193
02:07:36,571 --> 02:07:38,656
The queen killed herself
with a snake.

1194
02:07:38,740 --> 02:07:41,951
And just wait until you hear what
happened to our ancestors.

1195
02:07:42,035 --> 02:07:44,537
If you're very good,

1196
02:07:44,620 --> 02:07:48,666
tomorrow night I'll tell you
the story of Emperor Claudius.

1197
02:07:48,750 --> 02:07:51,461
He was betrayed...

1198
02:07:51,544 --> 02:07:53,796
by those closest to him.

1199
02:07:55,173 --> 02:07:57,091
By his own blood.

1200
02:07:58,676 --> 02:08:01,179
They whispered in dark corners...

1201
02:08:01,220 --> 02:08:03,181
and went out
late at night...

1202
02:08:03,222 --> 02:08:05,892
and conspired...

1203
02:08:05,975 --> 02:08:07,977
and conspired.

1204
02:08:09,520 --> 02:08:12,482
But the Emperor Claudius
knew that they were up to something.

1205
02:08:13,691 --> 02:08:16,027
He knew they were
busy little bees.

1206
02:08:18,071 --> 02:08:21,824
And one night he sat down
with one of them...

1207
02:08:21,908 --> 02:08:24,452
and he looked at her...

1208
02:08:24,535 --> 02:08:26,454
and he said,

1209
02:08:27,538 --> 02:08:30,708
"Tell me what you've been doing,

1210
02:08:30,750 --> 02:08:32,710
busy little bee,

1211
02:08:34,754 --> 02:08:38,007
or I shall strike down
those dearest to you.

1212
02:08:38,091 --> 02:08:42,512
You shall watch
as I bathe in their blood. "

1213
02:08:45,431 --> 02:08:48,226
And the Emperor
was heartbroken.

1214
02:08:50,144 --> 02:08:52,605
The little bee had
wounded him more deeply...

1215
02:08:52,647 --> 02:08:55,817
than anyone else
could ever have done.

1216
02:08:57,235 --> 02:09:01,155
And what do you think
happened then, Lucius?

1217
02:09:01,239 --> 02:09:03,658
I don't know, Uncle.

1218
02:09:09,247 --> 02:09:11,499
The little bee
told him everything.

1219
02:09:51,205 --> 02:09:54,834
Open, in the name of the Emperor!

1220
02:09:54,917 --> 02:09:56,836
Proximo!

1221
02:09:56,919 --> 02:10:00,381
Open the gates in the name
of the Emperor!

1222
02:10:00,465 --> 02:10:03,301
- Proximo!

1223
02:10:03,384 --> 02:10:06,012
Open the gates!

1224
02:10:11,851 --> 02:10:14,604
Open the gates, Proximo!

1225
02:10:14,646 --> 02:10:17,774
Do you want to die, old man?

1226
02:10:17,815 --> 02:10:20,109
Here.

1227
02:10:20,193 --> 02:10:22,487
Everything is prepared.

1228
02:10:22,570 --> 02:10:25,490
- It seems you've won your freedom.
- Proximo,

1229
02:10:25,573 --> 02:10:28,201
are you in danger
of becoming a good man?

1230
02:10:28,284 --> 02:10:29,952
Ha!

1231
02:10:33,247 --> 02:10:37,126
-Juba.
- All enemies of the Emperor die!

1232
02:10:37,210 --> 02:10:41,464
Open the gates!
The Emperor commands!

1233
02:10:45,301 --> 02:10:47,512
Pull!

1234
02:10:49,472 --> 02:10:52,475
Move! Two columns on the left!

1235
02:10:55,603 --> 02:10:58,398
I only need moments,
so do not be careless with your lives.

1236
02:10:58,481 --> 02:11:01,901
If you don't want any part of this,
go back to your cells.

1237
02:11:01,985 --> 02:11:03,903
We'll wait here for you,
Maximus.

1238
02:11:03,987 --> 02:11:06,864
- Strength and honor.
- Go!

1239
02:11:07,991 --> 02:11:10,910
Strength and honor.

1240
02:11:12,120 --> 02:11:15,665
Aim! Break the bars!

1241
02:12:21,898 --> 02:12:23,858
Shadows and dust.

1242
02:12:23,941 --> 02:12:25,985
Aah!

1243
02:13:04,315 --> 02:13:06,651
- Maximus!

1244
02:13:11,322 --> 02:13:13,366
I'm sorry.

1245
02:13:13,449 --> 02:13:15,743
No!

1246
02:13:40,018 --> 02:13:41,936
It's done.

1247
02:13:48,609 --> 02:13:51,112
And what of my nephew?

1248
02:13:51,154 --> 02:13:53,614
And what of his mother?

1249
02:13:55,491 --> 02:13:58,244
Should they share
her lover's fate?

1250
02:13:59,871 --> 02:14:02,332
Or should
I be merciful?

1251
02:14:04,625 --> 02:14:07,045
Commodus the Merciful.

1252
02:14:13,092 --> 02:14:16,262
Lucius will stay with me now.

1253
02:14:16,346 --> 02:14:19,557
And if his mother...

1254
02:14:19,640 --> 02:14:23,019
so much as looks at me...

1255
02:14:23,102 --> 02:14:26,064
in a manner that displeases me,

1256
02:14:27,357 --> 02:14:29,317
he will die.

1257
02:14:32,445 --> 02:14:34,697
If she decides...

1258
02:14:34,739 --> 02:14:37,325
to be noble...

1259
02:14:37,408 --> 02:14:40,953
and takes her own life,

1260
02:14:41,037 --> 02:14:42,955
he will die.

1261
02:14:45,750 --> 02:14:47,669
And as for you,

1262
02:14:50,546 --> 02:14:53,132
you will love me...

1263
02:14:53,216 --> 02:14:55,343
as I loved you.

1264
02:14:56,594 --> 02:14:59,055
You will provide me
with an heir...

1265
02:14:59,097 --> 02:15:01,391
of pure blood...

1266
02:15:01,432 --> 02:15:04,435
so that Commodus
and his progeny...

1267
02:15:04,477 --> 02:15:06,938
will rule for
a thousand years.

1268
02:15:11,067 --> 02:15:13,528
Am I not merciful?

1269
02:15:34,841 --> 02:15:37,260
Am I not merciful?

1270
02:15:49,480 --> 02:15:51,607
Maximus! Maximus!

1271
02:15:51,691 --> 02:15:54,527
Maximus! Maximus!
Maximus!

1272
02:15:54,569 --> 02:15:57,363
Maximus! Maximus!

1273
